The '''Hermitage Dam''' is a concrete [[gravity dam]] on the [[Wag Water River]] near [[Stony Hill, Jamaica|Stony Hill]] in [[Saint Andrew Parish, Jamaica|Saint Andrew Parish]], [[Jamaica]]. The primary purpose of the dam is to provide [[municipal water]] to nearby [[Kingston, Jamaica|Kingston]] and Saint Andrew Parish. Construction on the dam began in 1924 and it was inaugurated on 4 May 1927. It is owned by the [[National Irrigation Commission]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.discoverjamaica.com/gleaner/discover/geography/history6.htm | title=Jamaican History 6 | publisher=Discover Jamaica | accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.digjamaica.com/this_day_in_our_past/may_this_day_in_our_past/may_4 | title=May 4: "Hermitage Dam Completed" | publisher=Gleaner Company | accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref>

